    get_jaccard_from_self

    get_jaccard_from_self.Rd

    This function calculates jaccard distance for all pairwise comparison within one kmer_counts list object. If the parameter k is set, mash distance will be reported. Only jaccard distances will be reported if threshold is met.

    get_jaccard_from_self(
  kmer_counts_q,
  k = 6,
  min_jaccard = 0.01,
  use_rcpp = TRUE,
  use_sparse = TRUE,
  threads = 1,
  num_per_chunk_q = 50000,
  aa2int = FALSE
)

    Arguments

    kmer_counts_q

    kmer_counts

    k

    kmer length [default: 6]

    min_jaccard

    min jaccard distance to report [default: 0.01]

    use_rcpp

    use rcpp jaccard distance calculation[ default: TRUE]

    use_sparse

    use rcpp sparse approach [default: TRUE]

    threads

    number of parallel threads [default: 1]

    num_per_chunk_q

    specify max number per chunk q [default: 50000]

    aa2int

    convert aa to Int64 [default: FALSE]

    Value

    data.frame

    Author

    Kristian K Ullrich

    Examples

    data(hiv, package="MSA2dist")
l <- hiv |>
    MSA2dist::cds2aa() |>
    korthoR::count_kmers(k=6)
